# Commit Message Rules

When creating Git commit messages, always follow the format below.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <short description in Korean>
```

## Types

- feat: add a new feature
- fix: fix a bug
- docs: documentation changes
- style: code style changes (no logic impact)
- refactor: refactoring without behavior change
- test: add or update tests
- chore: build, config, tooling changes
- perf: performance improvements

## Rules

- `type` must be lowercase English
- Description must be concise and in Korean (within ~50 characters)
- Do not start with English verbs like "Add", "Update", "Fix"

## Examples

✅ feat(auth): 소셜 로그인 기능 추가
✅ fix(api): 사용자 조회 에러 수정
✅ chore(rules): 커밋 메시지 룰 추가
✅ chore(config): ESLint 설정 추가

❌ Add 소셜 로그인
❌ Update 설정 파일
